  "text": "In image retrieval, burstiness is the phenomenon in which certain visual word appears many times in an image and it leads to multiple matches. Multiple matches generally exist in human images matching because of the self-similarity of clothes where same word appears many times in an image. Multiple matches cause great impact on matching accuracy as discussed in [CITATION_1] , because cosine similarity, i.e. the dot product operation, is applied to compute matching score between two images. For instance, the occurrences of word c i in image I x and I y are 1 and 9, respectively. Then the matching score of c i is 9. That is to say, the descriptor in image I x matches 9 descriptors in image I y and votes 9 times. It is the dot product that leads multiple matching phenomenon to a high score between two dissimilar images.",
